# vw_mr_report_payload — View Specification
## M+R Audit PDF Report Assembly View

---

## Purpose

This view assembles the complete, flat, merge-field-keyed payload for a given `assessment_id` that WF-MR-03 uses to populate the PDF report template. It must return exactly one row per assessment, with every merge field resolved to its final display value. WF-MR-03 reads this view once and uses the result to execute all find-and-replace operations against the Google Docs template copy.

---

## Design Principles

- One row per `assessment_id`
- Every column name maps directly to a `{{MERGE_FIELD}}` token in the report template
- All GPT output rows from `gm_assessment_gpt_outputs` are pivoted into named columns (not returned as array rows)
- All percentage values are formatted as display strings (e.g. `'74%'` not `0.74`)
- All nullable fields must return empty string `''` rather than `NULL` to prevent broken merge tokens
- Stage label must be the human-readable display name, not the `stage_id` FK value
- Cross-section labels must be the human-readable `cross_section_label`, not the `cross_section_id`

